Lagos State Government, on Wednesday, discharged 37 more COVID-19 patients from its isolation facilities, bringing the total number of recoveries to 358. Announcing this on its Twitter handle, Lagos State Ministry of Health explained that 19 of the patients were females, while 18 are males, including an Indian national. #COVID19Lagos Update
